---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Fusion 360 Model Export Guide | Josh Bonomini" 
  description="Learn how to export Fusion 360 models for use with the model-viewer component"
>
  <main class="min-h-screen bg-base-50 dark:bg-base-900">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16">
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-base-900 dark:text-white mb-8">
        Using Fusion 360 Models with the Portfolio Site
      </h1>
      
      <div class="prose prose-base-900 dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
        <p class="lead text-lg text-base-700 dark:text-base-300">
          This guide explains how to export Fusion 360 models for use with the <code>&lt;model-viewer&gt;</code> component used on the portfolio site.
        </p>
        
        <h2>Supported Formats</h2>
        <p>
          The <code>&lt;model-viewer&gt;</code> component used on this site supports 3D models in the following formats:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>glTF/GLB</strong> (preferred format) - Binary format that includes geometry, textures, animations</li>
          <li><strong>USDZ</strong> (for iOS AR experiences)</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2>Exporting from Fusion 360</h2>
        
        <h3>Method 1: Direct Export to glTF/GLB</h3>
        <ol>
          <li>In Fusion 360, go to <strong>File &gt; Export</strong></li>
          <li>Select <strong>glTF (.gltf, .glb)</strong> as the file format</li>
          <li>Choose <strong>GLB</strong> option for a single binary file (recommended)</li>
          <li>Configure export settings:
            <ul>
              <li>Enable <strong>Export textures</strong> if your model has materials</li>
              <li>Set appropriate scale (usually meters)</li>
              <li>Choose which components to include</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>Click <strong>Export</strong> and save the file</li>
        </ol>
        
        <h3>Method 2: Using an Intermediate Format</h3>
        <p>If direct glTF export isn't available in your version:</p>
        <ol>
          <li>Export your model as <strong>OBJ</strong> format from Fusion 360</li>
          <li>Use an online converter like <a href="https://gltf.report/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-accent-600 hover:text-accent-700 dark:text-accent-400 dark:hover:text-accent-300">glTF Tools</a> or <a href="https://sketchfab.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-accent-600 hover:text-accent-700 dark:text-accent-400 dark:hover:text-accent-300">Sketchfab</a> to convert OBJ to glTF/GLB</li>
        </ol>
        
        <h2>Adding Models to the Portfolio</h2>
        <ol>
          <li>Place your exported <code>.glb</code> file in a web-accessible location (like GitHub Pages or other hosting)</li>
          <li>Create a new JSON file in <code>src/content/models/</code> following this template:
            <pre><code>{
  "title": "Your Model Name",
  "modelUrl": "https://path-to-your-model/model.glb",
  "posterUrl": "https://path-to-your-thumbnail/thumbnail.webp", 
  "description": "Description of your model",
  "ar": true,
  "autoRotate": true,
  "cameraControls": true,
  "tags": ["fusion360", "your-tags"]
}</code></pre>
          </li>
        </ol>
        
        <h2>Creating Preview Images</h2>
        <p>For the <code>posterUrl</code>, you can:</p>
        <ol>
          <li>Take a screenshot of your model in Fusion 360</li>
          <li>Convert the image to WebP format for better performance</li>
          <li>Host it alongside your GLB file</li>
        </ol>
        
        <h2>Optimizing Models</h2>
        <p>For better web performance:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Simplify complex geometries</li>
          <li>Aim for file sizes under 10MB</li>
          <li>Use compressed textures</li>
          <li>Remove unnecessary components</li>
        </ul>
        
        <div class="mt-12 border-t border-base-200 dark:border-base-700 pt-8">
          <a href="/BonominiBlog/models/" class="inline-flex items-center text-accent-600 dark:text-accent-400 hover:underline">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5 mr-2" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M10 19l-7-7m0 0l7-7m-7 7h18" />
            </svg>
            Back to Models
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
